_dc:description: The name or code for the project associated with the relevé
The description (not a code) of the plant community or vegetation unit associated with the relevé
The compass direction that the relevé site faces
The angle of inclination of the relevé site in degrees, rounded to the nearest whole number
The total cover (%) of all plants, rounded to the nearest hundredth (2 decimal places)
The  cover (%) of trees, rounded to the nearest hundredth (2 decimal places)
The  cover (%) of shrubs, rounded to the nearest hundredth (2 decimal places)
The  cover (%) of the herb layer, rounded to the nearest hundredth (2 decimal places)
The  cover (%) of cryptogams, rounded to the nearest hundredth (2 decimal places)
The  cover (%) of mosses, rounded to the nearest hundredth (2 decimal places)
The  cover (%) of lichens, rounded to the nearest hundredth (2 decimal places)
The  cover (%) of algae, rounded to the nearest hundredth (2 decimal places)
The  cover (%) of litter, rounded to the nearest hundredth (2 decimal places)
The  cover (%) of open water, rounded to the nearest hundredth (2 decimal places)
The  cover (%) of bare rock, rounded to the nearest hundredth (2 decimal places)
The height in meters of the tree layer, rounded to the nearest whole number
The height in meters of the shrub layer, can be written in decimal notation
The height in centimeters of the high herb layer, rounded to the nearest whole number
The value is true if mosses in the releve were identified
The value is true if lichens in the releve were identified
